text: my name is Eric Johnson and I'm the CEO
of Datasaur and our platform is built
for NLP annotation and LLM evaluation
and deployment uh we work in the
generative AI space but we haven't
always been in that space historically
our focus has been on text annotation
and labeling structuring to build out
things like chat bots for financial use
cases healthcare legal use cases etc
even customer service but the way
generative AI has changed everything has
transformed NLP into language modeling
there are NLP components natural
language processing components still
involved in language modeling when it
comes to text annotation that is still
highly relevant to reward modeling
fine-tuning so that you can train uh a
chatbot or a machine a computer to
interact with people a certain way and
so the NLP part of what we used to do is
still a core focus of what we offer but
generative AI has changed dramatically
the way in which our customers interact
with us because they want a full service
deployment from the annotation all the
way to the agent that they want to serve
their customers the biggest advantage
that AWS has with us is that we have the
most intuitive NLP language model
platform on the market when they get
customers that want to come in and they
want to use something that's touchless
or frictionless small project to big
enterprise then AWS can sell us if they
don't have another solution that can
match it and so that brings us both
business and then on the flip side of
that for the customers that's uh an
acceleration of their timelines a

and so everybody wins
